        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During one winter, the roads in a rural area were completely free from snow when it started snowing at midnight. It snowed heavily all night and day. By {@a@} a.m. it was {@b@} cm deep. To save money the local authorities wait until the snow is {@c@} cm deep before ploughing the snow away from the roads. Forecast how many hours and minutes after midnight the ploughing should start [[input:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]] [[input:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]][[validation:ans1]] [[validation:ans2]], enter the number of assumptions you have made [[input:ans3]][[validation:ans3]][[feedback:prt3]] to check your assumptions.
 &lt;ol&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;If the depth of snow is represented by &lt;em&gt;D&lt;/em&gt; cm and the time by &lt;em&gt;t&lt;/em&gt; hours after midnight then a linear model for the depth as a function of time may be written:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;D&lt;/em&gt; = &lt;em&gt;at&lt;/em&gt; + &lt;em&gt;b&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;where &lt;em&gt;a&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;b&lt;/em&gt; are constants to be found from the other information in the problem or from assumptions. As there was no snow at midnight &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; 0 = 0 + &lt;em&gt;b&lt;/em&gt;    or     &lt;em&gt;b&lt;/em&gt;= 0&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is stated that &lt;em&gt;D&lt;/em&gt; = {@b@} when &lt;em&gt;t&lt;/em&gt; = {@a@}, i.e.&lt;/p&gt;
{@b@} = {@a@}&lt;em&gt;a&lt;/em&gt;     or &lt;em&gt;a&lt;/em&gt; = {@b@}/{@a@}&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So the equation for estimating the depth of snow at different times is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;D&lt;/em&gt; = {@b@}&lt;em&gt;t&lt;/em&gt;/{@a@}&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The model will predict a level of {@c@}cm at a time &lt;em&gt;t&lt;/em&gt; given by&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;{@c@} ={@b@} &lt;em&gt;t&lt;/em&gt; / {@a@}     or    &lt;em&gt;t&lt;/em&gt; = {@c@}*{@a@}/{@b@} = {@d@}&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;i.e.  The snow plough will be needed {@ta1@} hours and {@ta2@} after midnight.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assumptions:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assume snow build up is steady&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No drifts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Assume that the snow is constant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Assume change in the time of the day does not affect the situation&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
